Overview
• Hybrid AI system integrating machine learning based diabetes prediction with Retrieval Augmented Generation grounded in ADA clinical guidelines.
• Extends prediction into structured clinical action plans based on retrieved guideline content.
• Designed for conference level research standards.

Objectives
• Accurately predict diabetes risk using supervised machine learning.
• Provide structured clinical recommendations grounded in ADA guidelines.
• Ensure dual layer explainability at model and retrieval levels.
• Reduce hallucination by constraining generation to retrieved context.

Diabetes Prediction Layer
• Models evaluated: Logistic Regression, Random Forest, Gradient Boosting, XGBoost.
• Final model: Nested Cross Validated XGBoost.
• Evaluation metrics: Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1 Score, ROC AUC.
• Outputs include prediction label, probability score, and risk category.

Model Explainability
• SHAP used for feature contribution analysis.
• Confusion matrix visualization included.
• Summary plot for global feature importance.

Guideline Grounded RAG Layer
• Multiple ADA guideline chapters used including Diagnosis, Glycemic Goals, Pharmacologic Treatment, CVD Risk Management, CKD, and Complications.
• Content cleaned and processed for semantic retrieval.

Retrieval Architecture
• Embedding model: BAAI bge large en v1.5.
• Vector database: FAISS.
• Semantic similarity used to retrieve relevant guideline sections.

Generator Model
• LLM used: Mistral 7B Instruct v0.2.
• Generates structured clinical recommendations grounded in retrieved ADA content. Structured Clinical Output
• Core Recommendation.
• First Line Therapy Details.
• Escalation or Combination Therapy Guidance.
• Key Clinical Considerations.
• Supporting Guideline Phrase.
• Confidence Level.

Retrieval Transparency
• Displays chapter name.
• Displays similarity score.
• Shows preview of retrieved guideline text.
• Ensures traceability between recommendation and source.

Implementation Details
• Platform: Google Colab with GPU.
• FAISS index saved and loaded from Google Drive.
• Model saving and loading implemented for reproducibility.
• Dataset and guideline PDFs provided via external links.

Research Contributions
• Hybrid ML and guideline grounded LLM architecture.
• Dual layer explainability framework.
• Structured clinical action generation.
• Reduction of hallucination through constrained RAG.

Limitations
• Dependent on quality of guideline chunking.
• No direct clinical validation yet.
• Not intended for real world medical decision making without expert oversight.  Future Work
• Multi guideline comparison studies.
• Clinical expert validation.
• Hallucination scoring metrics.
• Streamlit based deployment interface.
